   We proposed a feature-rich approach to the under-investigated problem of predicting essay-level prompt adherence scores on student essays.
  </a>
  <a href="#1" id="1">
   In an evaluation on 830 argumentative essays selected from the ICLE corpus, our system significantly outperformed a Random Indexing based baseline by several evaluation metrics.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   To stimulate further research on this task, we make all our annotations, including our prompt adherence scores, the LDA topic annotations, and the error annotations publicly available.
